---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Why it matters"
  description="Why OpenBurnBar exists — avoid bill shock, understand agent spend, know quota before workflows fail, recover context fast, keep core data local."
>
  <section class="pagehead">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--ember">Why it matters</span>
      <h1 class="pagehead__h">
        Multi-agent work needs <span class="ember">multi-agent visibility.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lead">
        You don't run one model anymore. You run Claude in one tab, Codex in
        another, Cursor and Copilot in the editor, and Factory or Forge on the
        side. Spend is fractured across vendors and time zones, quotas don't
        share a clock, and "why did the bill explode" arrives on the first
        of the month.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="benefits">
    <div class="container container--wide">
      <ul class="benefits__grid">
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B1</div>
          <h3>Avoid bill shock.</h3>
          <p>
            See today's burn the moment you sit down. See this week's pattern.
            See where it's going before the invoice rounds the corner.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B2</div>
          <h3>Understand agent spend.</h3>
          <p>
            Cost broken down by provider, by model, by session, by project.
            Which model burned the most cache? Which agent doubled
            this week? OpenBurnBar answers — locally.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B3</div>
          <h3>Know quota before workflows fail.</h3>
          <p>
            Five-hour windows. Weekly windows. Plan-tier ceilings. Lane-aware
            counters. OpenBurnBar reads them all and tells you which one is
            about to roll before your agent hits a wall.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit benefit--ember">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B3·5</div>
          <h3>Never run out of quota mid-task.</h3>
          <p>
            The <a href="/router" class="benefit__link">Fire Hydrant</a> — our
            local multi-provider router — sends Cursor, Factory, and Forge
            traffic through one gateway and shifts to the next healthy account
            the moment one rate-limits or runs out. Five-minute cool-downs.
            Round-robin by least-recently-used. No 429s land in your IDE.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B4</div>
          <h3>Recover context fast.</h3>
          <p>
            Sessions, projects, streams, tool calls, retrieval — all indexed
            locally. When something goes sideways, you can replay the run,
            inspect the tool trace, and pick up where the agent left off.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B5</div>
          <h3>Keep core data local.</h3>
          <p>
            Your sessions never have to leave your machine. The cloud is an
            opt-in convenience, not a requirement. Disconnect the network and
            the product keeps working.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B6</div>
          <h3>Use the cloud only when it helps.</h3>
          <p>
            When you want hosted quota refresh from a phone or a backed-up
            conversation across devices, the cloud is there — gated by
            Apple-verified entitlement and end-to-end encryption.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B7</div>
          <h3>Operate agents responsibly.</h3>
          <p>
            Whether you're a solo developer or a small team, OpenBurnBar makes
            the cost of every agent legible. The dashboard is the operating
            layer that lets you keep spending sane.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="benefit">
          <div class="benefit__num mono">B8</div>
          <h3>Trust by inspection.</h3>
          <p>
            MIT-licensed. The threat model is in the repo. Provider claims
            cite the file and line of the adapter. You can read every promise
            in code, not just in copy.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="endcta endcta--inline">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h2>The bill is going to find you anyway.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Read it on your own terms.
      </p>
      <div class="endcta__ctas">
        <a class="btn btn--ember" href="/download">Download for macOS <span class="btn-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/product">Tour the product</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .pagehead { padding-block: var(--s-9) var(--s-6); }
  .pagehead__h { margin-top: var(--s-3); max-width: 18ch; }
  .pagehead .lead { margin-top: var(--s-4); max-width: 64ch; }
  .benefits { padding-block: var(--s-9); border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line); }
  .benefits__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--s-5);
  }
  .benefit {
    padding: var(--s-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
    border-radius: var(--r-4);
    background: var(--ink-base);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--s-2);
  }
  .benefit__num { color: var(--ember-bright); font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; }
  .benefit h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    color: var(--text-bright);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 36, "wght" 540;
    letter-spacing: -0.014em;
  }
  .benefit p { color: var(--text-base); }
  .benefit--ember {
    border-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--ember-core) 35%, var(--ink-line));
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 106, 26, 0.05) 0%, var(--ink-base) 100%);
    position: relative;
    box-shadow: 0 12px 32px -20px rgba(255, 106, 26, 0.4);
  }
  .benefit--ember .benefit__num { color: var(--ember-bright); }
  .benefit__link {
    color: var(--ember-bright);
    border-bottom: 1px dashed color-mix(in oklab, var(--ember-bright) 40%, var(--ink-line));
  }
  .benefit__link:hover {
    color: var(--ember-glow);
    border-bottom-color: var(--ember-bright);
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) { .benefits__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .endcta--inline {
    padding-block: var(--s-9);
    text-align: center;
    background:
      radial-gradient(60% 80% at 50% 50%, rgba(255, 106, 26, 0.05), transparent 70%);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink-line);
  }
  .endcta--inline h2 { margin-bottom: var(--s-3); }
  .endcta__ctas { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: var(--s-3); margin-top: var(--s-5); flex-wrap: wrap; }
</style>
